description.plain:
The Ghost Town DJs' one-hit wonder, “My Boo,” is about a girl fantasizing about a guy. The song is the only record Ghost Town DJ’s ever released.

The song peaked at #31 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1996. 20 years later, it had a resurgence, and rose to #27 due to the #runningmanchallenge.

The Running Man dance was originally posted on Instagram by New Jersey high school students Kevin Vincent and Jeremiah Hall. Shortly after their post, Maryland Terrapins' college basketball team issued the #runningmanchallenge. It has become a viral sensation in 2016, as more  college athletes, and even pros attempt to exhibit their shuffling skills.

Vincent and Hall explained how the dance came about on The Ellen Show.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ul7TZy9_fo4
